    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When one of your team children within 60 feet who can see or hear you fails a d20 Test by 2 or less without rolling a natural 1, you can take a Reaction to call out a quick bit of advice, make an emphatic gesture, or use a more subtle technique to guide away from failure. If you do, the team child gains a +2 bonus on their check, changing the result to a success. However, your focus on your team child distracts you from your own challenges. On your next turn, your speed is halved, and you can use either an action or a bonus action, not both.</p>",
